Beau Biden, son of Vice President Joe Biden, has passed away after battling brain cancer. The Biden family announced the news and expressed their deep sadness. They believe that Beau's spirit will live on through his wife and children. Beau's life was marked by service to others, including working to establish the rule of law in Kosovo and serving in the Iraq War. As Delaware's Attorney General, he fought for the powerless and protected children from abuse. The Biden family describes Beau as a role model and the finest man they have ever known.